        <div class="caption">
            <strong>Figure 1.</strong> Conceptual framework illustrating the systematic inequity in ECE teacher preparation programs. The model demonstrates how institutional theories inform understanding of systemic mechanisms that create negative outcomes, necessitating comprehensive reforms. The central organizing principle highlights the tension between professional specialization needs and institutional inertia. Solid arrows indicate direct causal pathways, while dashed arrows represent feedback loops that perpetuate or challenge the system. This framework integrates institutional theory, professional capital theory, and pedagogical coherence theory to explain the complex dynamics of faculty recruitment, professional competency, and educational quality in Ghana's Colleges of Education ECE programs.
